<div class="accordion">
    <div class="header">Ethics Certificate</div>
	<div class="content">
	<div class="tab8 parsys"><div class="text uiwText parbase section">








   


 









 


 


   
    <!-- 
    **note changes made above in normal non preview css styles
    repeat the style writing above and append X at the end of the component id for preview
     --> 
   
    
    <div id="toolbarObj332726715" class="allToolbarSelector"></div>
    
    
    
    
<script>                                                       

</script>
<div id="component332726715" class="textComponent">  

<div class="text"><p>The Philosophy Department offers a&nbsp;<a href="https://continuing.ryerson.ca/public/category/courseCategoryCertificateProfile.do?method=load&amp;certificateId=175366" target="_blank">Certificate in Ethics</a>, which consists of 6 courses (2 required and 4 elective). You do not need to be enrolled in a degree program at Ryerson to enroll in this Certificate. If you are currently enrolled in a Ryerson degree program, and if some of the courses listed in the Certificate in Ethics are part of&nbsp;<a href="/currentstudents/calendars/">your program's curriculum</a>, you may count 3 of these towards the Certificate.</p>
</div>

<div style="clear:both;"></div>
</div>     
   












</div>

</div>

	</div>
	</div>

<div class="accordion">
    <div class="header">Part-Time Studies</div>
	<div class="content">
	<div class="tab9 parsys"><div class="text uiwText parbase section">








   


 









 


 


   
    <!-- 
    **note changes made above in normal non preview css styles
    repeat the style writing above and append X at the end of the component id for preview
     --> 
   
    
    <div id="toolbarObj1757346285" class="allToolbarSelector"></div>
    
    
    
    
<script>                                                       

</script>
<div id="component1757346285" class="textComponent">  

<div class="text"><p>Ryerson's&nbsp;<a href="https://continuing.ryerson.ca/" target="_blank">G. Raymond Chang School of Continuing Education</a>&nbsp;offers a&nbsp;<a href="https://continuing.ryerson.ca/search/publicCourseAdvancedSearch.do?method=doPaginatedSearch&amp;showInternal=false&amp;cspIndex=true&amp;isPageDisplayed=true&amp;courseSearch.courseDescriptionKeyword=&amp;courseSearch.disciplineCode=&amp;courseSearch.partialCourseNumber=&amp;courseSearch.courseCategoryStringArray=0&amp;courseSearch.sectionSemesterIdString=&amp;courseSearch.programStreamStringArray=18707&amp;courseSearch.deliveryMethodString=&amp;courseSearch.sectionDayOfWeekStringArray=0&amp;courseSearch.sectionStartTimeStringArray=0&amp;courseSearch.sectionStartMonthStringArray=0" target="_blank">wide range of Philosophy courses</a>. These are available for part-time students, and also for full-time students who are attracted to the School's evening, spring/summer, and distance formats. If you are currently enrolled in an undergraduate degree program, make sure that any courses you take from the Chang School are listed on your program's curriculum in the Ryerson&nbsp;<a href="/currentstudents/calendars/" target="_blank">Undergraduate Calendar</a>. Any courses you take that are not part of your program's curriculum will not normally be counted towards your degree.</p>
</div>

<div style="clear:both;"></div>
</div>     
   












</div>

</div>

