<div id="component448964561" class="textComponent">  

<div class="text"><h2>Awards Available to Philosophy BA Students</h2></div>

<div style="clear:both;"></div>
</div>     
   












</div>
<div class="text uiwText parbase section">








   


 









 


 


   
    <!-- 
    **note changes made above in normal non preview css styles
    repeat the style writing above and append X at the end of the component id for preview
     --> 
   
    
    <div id="toolbarObj555853291" class="allToolbarSelector"></div>
    
    
    
    
<script>                                                       

</script>
<div id="component555853291" class="textComponent">  

<div class="text"><p>&nbsp;<br>
To be eligible for these awards, you must be enrolled in either the BA in Philosophy, or in a double-major program where one of those majors is Philosophy.<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>The <strong>Community Service Award</strong> honours a student who has made outstanding achievements in one or more of the following: cultivating the Philosophy community at Ryerson University; acting as an ambassador of the Philosophy or Double Major program both within the Ryerson community and/or externally; serving in governance roles such as program councils and Senate; collaborating internally and externally on initiatives that promote the BA Philosophy or double-major program or enhance the student experience. Value: $500<br>
</li>
<li>The <strong>Bronze Essay Award</strong> recognizes an excellent essay written by a student in one of his or her Philosophy courses. Value: $250.</li>
<li>The <strong>Silver Essay Award</strong>&nbsp;recognizes&nbsp;an excellent essay written by a student in one of his or her Philosophy courses. Value: $300.<br>
</li>
<li>The <strong>Gold Essay Award</strong> is given for the best essay written by a student in one of his or her Philosophy courses. Value: $500.<br>
</li>
<li>The <strong>First Year Academic Excellence Award in Philosophy </strong>recognizes the outstanding academic performance by a first year philosophy student. Value: $500.<br>
</li>
<li>The <strong>Second Year Academic Excellence Award in Philosophy</strong> recognizes the outstanding academic performance by a second year philosophy student. Value: $500.<br>
</li>
<li>The <strong>Third Year Academic Excellence Award in Philosophy </strong>recognizes the outstanding academic performance by a third year philosophy student. Value: $500.<br>
</li>
<li>The <strong>Fourth Year Academic Excellence Award in Philosophy </strong>recognizes the outstanding academic performance by a fourth year philosophy student. Value: $500.</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>
<a href="/content/dam/philosophy/BA-Award-Winners.pdf" target="_blank">[PDF] Previous Award-Winners</a><br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>Students in the Philosophy BA program (or in a a double-major that involves philosophy) may also be eligible for additional <a href="/registrar/students/scholarships/">university-wide scholarships and awards</a>, as well as <a href="/arts/students/undergraduate-programs/scholarships-and-awards/">Faculty of Arts scholarships, awards, and grants</a>.<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div style="clear:both;"></div>
</div>     
   












</div>
<div class="title section">









<a class="defaultPageTitle">Study Abroad Opportunity - The Italy Credit Program</a></div>
<div class="text uiwText parbase section">








   


 









 


 


   
    <!-- 
    **note changes made above in normal non preview css styles
    repeat the style writing above and append X at the end of the component id for preview
     --> 
   
    
    <div id="toolbarObj1053770163" class="allToolbarSelector"></div>
    
    
    
    
<script>                                                       

</script>
<div id="component1053770163" class="textComponent">  

<div class="text"><p>&nbsp;<br /> Most years, Ryerson Philosophy students will have the opportunity of going abroad and earning 3 course credits towards their BA requirements through the Italy Credit Program in partnership with Vancouver Island University.</p> 
<p><a href="https://socialsciences.viu.ca/liberal-studies/liberal-studies-abroad">The Italy Credit Program</a> provides an exciting and stimulating interdisciplinary examination of one of the most dynamic and significant periods in the history of European culture. The setting - the city of Florence - is particularly suitable because of its immense contribution to the Renaissance, the 15th and 16th century reawakening of humanistic learning and artistic endeavour.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>This program has been designed so that you can earn 3 course credits during the spring without interfering with your normal Fall and Winter terms.</p> 
<p>Information workshops will normally be held in October of each year.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>Detailed information about the program can be found <a href="https://socialsciences.viu.ca/liberal-studies/italy-2017-programme-discover-renaissance-0">here</a>.</p> 
<p>For more information, please contact Prof. John Caruana at <a href="mailto:jcaruana@ryerson.ca">jcaruana@ryerson.ca</a>.</p> 
<p>For other international opportunities, see the <a href="/philosophy/students/current/">Student Handbook.</a><br /> &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p></div>

<div style="clear:both;"></div>
</div>     
   












</div>

